(The flipped classroom model places new instruction at home through video lectures and) Tj
T* (reserves in-class time for exercises, projects, and discussions. Research indicates that) Tj
T* (students who engage actively with material through collaborative problem-solving) Tj
T* (demonstrate significantly higher retention rates compared to passive listening. The teacher's) Tj
T* (role shifts from lecturer to facilitator, providing targeted assistance while students work) Tj
T* (through higher-order thinking tasks.) Tj
